'''Miroslav Koubek''' (born 1 September 1951) is a Czech professional [[Manager (association football)|football manager]] and former [[Football player|player]] who played as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]]. He currently manages the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]]. He won the [[Czech First League]] with [[FC Viktoria Plzeň|Viktoria Plzeň]] in the [[2014–15 Czech First League|2014–15 season]].

==Coaching career==
Koubek coached several Czech clubs. He led [[SK Kladno]] to the [[Czech 2. Liga|Czech Second League]] title in the [[2005–06 Czech 2. Liga|2005–06 season]], securing the club's return to top-flight football for the first time since 1970.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/domaci-souteze/kladno-postoupilo-po-36-letech-do-prvni-ligy.A060517_191429_fot_dsouteze_no|title=Kladno postoupilo po 36 letech do první ligy|language=cs|date=17 May 2006|work=[[iDNES.cz]]|accessdate=10 May 2025|publisher=[[Mafra (company)|Mafra]]}}</ref> In the [[2008–09 Czech 2. Liga|2008–09 season]], he led [[FC Zenit Čáslav]] to second place in the Czech Second League and promotion to the First League,<ref>{{cite web |last=Pospíšil |first=Ladislav |title=Koubek potvrdil, že jde do Baníku |url=https://kutnohorsky.denik.cz/fotbal_region/koubek-potvrdil-ze-jde-do-baniku20090602.html |website=[[Deník]] |access-date=10 May 2025 |language=cs |date=2 June 2009|publisher=[[Vltava Labe Media]]}}</ref> although Čáslav eventually sold the First League license to rivals and remained in the Second League.<ref>{{cite web |title=Slovácko se vrací do ligy, koupilo postup od Čáslavi |url=https://www.denik.cz/fotbal/caslav-ma-licenci-ted-je-na-rade-prodej-postupu.html |website=[[Deník]] |access-date=10 May 2025 |language=cs |date=10 June 2009|publisher=[[Vltava Labe Media]]}}</ref> Koubek joined [[FC Baník Ostrava]] in June 2009, leading them to third place in the [[2009–10 Czech First League]]. The [[2010–11 Czech First League|2010–11 season]] however started with miserable results for Baník, with the club losing seven of the opening 13 matches, and Koubek was sacked in October.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fotbal.idnes.cz/fotbaliste-ostravy-jsou-bez-trenera-koubek-byl-po-dalsi-prohre-odvolan-135-/fotbal.aspx?c=A101025_105919_ostrava-sport_jab|title=Fotbalisté Ostravy jsou bez trenéra, Koubek byl po další prohře odvolán|language=cs|date=25 October 2010|work=[[iDNES.cz]]|accessdate=3 August 2011|publisher=[[Mafra (company)|Mafra]]}}</ref>

Koubek returned to the Czech First League as the manager of [[FK Mladá Boleslav|Mladá Boleslav]] on 28 May 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fotbal.idnes.cz/boleslav-oznamila-noveho-kouce-na-prvoligovou-scenu-se-vraci-koubek-1gb-/fotbal.asp?c=A110528_212853_fotbal_min|title=Boleslav oznámila nového kouče, na prvoligovou scénu se vrací Koubek|language=cs|date=28 May 2011|work=[[iDNES.cz]]|accessdate=29 May 2011|publisher=[[Mafra (company)|Mafra]]}}</ref> Koubek led Boleslav to fourth place in the [[2011–12 Czech First League]] and qualification for the following season's [[UEFA Europa League]]. However, after a run of three consecutive league defeats, he resigned from his position in September 2012.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://fotbal.idnes.cz/miroslav-koubek-rezignace-mlada-boleslav-fpw-/fotbal.aspx?c=A120915_211905_fotbal_pes|title=Mladá Boleslav je bez trenéra, Koubek po porážce rezignoval|language=cs|work=[[iDNES.cz]]|date=15 September 2012|accessdate=26 October 2012|publisher=[[Mafra (company)|Mafra]]}}</ref> Koubek was appointed to the manager's position at [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] in September 2013 following the resignation of former boss [[Michal Petrouš]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.rozhlas.cz/zpravy/fotbal/_zprava/po-petrousovi-povede-fotbalovou-slavii-miroslav-koubek--1258757|title=Po Petroušovi povede fotbalovou Slavii Miroslav Koubek|language=cs|publisher=Czech Radio|date=18 September 2013|accessdate=2 December 2013}}</ref> He was sacked in March 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title=Šok ve Slavii! Nové vedení vyhodilo trenéra Koubka, nahradí ho Holanďan|url=http://www.gambrinusliga.cz/clanek/4226-ok-ve-slavii-nov-veden-vyhodilo-trenra-koubka-nahrad-ho-holanan.html|work=Gambrinus liga|accessdate=3 March 2014|author1=Huml, Ondřej|author2=Stránský, Luděk|language=cs|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140303165129/http://www.gambrinusliga.cz/clanek/4226-ok-ve-slavii-nov-veden-vyhodilo-trenra-koubka-nahrad-ho-holanan.html|archive-date=3 March 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>

In August 2014, Koubek became the new manager of [[FC Viktoria Plzeň]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radio.cz/en/section/news/plzen-name-koubek-manager-day-after-sacking-uhrin|title=Plzeň name Koubek manager day after sacking Uhrin|first=Ian|last=Willoughby|work=[[Radio Prague]]|date=12 August 2014|accessdate=16 November 2014}}</ref> and in May 2015 won his first league title. In July 2015 he celebrated the [[Czech Supercup]] with his side, who defeated Liberec 2–1.<ref>{{cite web |title=Plzeň zdolala Liberec a získala Superpohár. Koubek: Budeme v pohodě |url=https://www.denik.cz/fotbal/plzen-zdolala-liberec-superpohar-ji-vystrelili-horava-a-kolar-20150718.html |website=[[Deník]] |access-date=10 May 2025 |language=cs |date=18 July 2015|publisher=[[Vltava Labe Media]]}}</ref> In spite of his league success, Plzeň only won once in their first four league matches of the [[2015–16 Czech First League|2015–16 season]] and were eliminated in the qualifying rounds of the Champions League, culminating in his departure from the role by mutual consent in mid-August 2015.<ref>{{cite web |title=Plzeň mění trenéra: Koubek skončil, Krejčí a Horváth mají probudit tým |url=https://www.denik.cz/fotbal/koubek-v-plzni-konci-nahradi-ho-krejci-pomahat-mu-bude-horvath-20150816.html |website=[[Deník]] |access-date=10 May 2025 |language=cs |date=16 August 2015|publisher=[[Vltava Labe Media]]}}</ref>

On 30 May 2016, Koubek was announced as the new manager of [[Bohemians 1905]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bohemians.cz/clanek/17845/miroslav-koubek-trenerem-bohemians.aspx|title=Miroslav Koubek trenérem Bohemians - Vedení klubu dnes představilo nového trenéra A mužstva.|language=cs|work=[[Bohemians 1905]]|accessdate=30 May 2016}}</ref> Koubek was appointed to the manager's position at [[FC Hradec Králové|Hradec Králové]] in June 2021 following the resignation of manager [[Zdenko Frťala]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/novacka-hradec-kralove-povede-v-prvni-fotbalove-lize-trener-koubek/2045321|title=Nováčka Hradec Králové povede v první fotbalové lize trenér Koubek|language=cs|work=ČeskéNoviny.cz|accessdate=1 June 2021|agency=[[Czech News Agency]]}}</ref> In June 2023, Koubek returned to Plzeň for a third spell in charge of the club, signing a one-year contract, which made him the oldest coach in the league.<ref>{{cite news |first1=Miloslav|last1=Novák|first2=Ervín|last2=Schulz|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/prvni-liga/trener-miroslav-koubek-viktoria-plzen-navrat.A230602_161640_fotbal_min|title=Plzeň povede nejstarší kouč v lize. Koubek má roční smlouvu a asistenta Trousila|language=cs|work=[[iDNES.cz]]|date=5 June 2023|accessdate=10 May 2025|publisher=[[Mafra (company)|Mafra]]}}</ref>

On 19 December 2025, Koubek was hired as manager of [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Nový kouč reprezentace je konečně tady. Koubek ji převzal jako nejstarší trenér vůbec|url=https://www.eurofotbal.cz/clanky/novy-kouc-reprezentace-je-konecne-tady-koubek-ji-prevzal-jako-nejstarsi-trener-vubec-798896/|website=EuroFotbal.cz|date=19 December 2025|access-date=21 December 2025|language=cs}}</ref> In March 2026, he led his nation to qualification for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] after winning both play-off ties on penalties against the [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]] and [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]] in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA second round|2026 World Cup qualification European play-off round]], marking their first appearance since 2006.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/european-qualifiers/news/02a3-2047bcf476d8-369543fe9786-1000--czechia-2-2-denmark-highlights-3-1-on-pens-czechia-book-202/ |title=Czechia 2-2 Denmark highlights (3-1 on pens): Czechia book 2026 World Cup spot with play-off final win |website=uefa.com|publisher=[[UEFA]]|date=31 March 2026 |access-date=31 March 2026}}</ref>

